cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a model for image classification that uses verification with reference images instead of memorizing all candidate classes. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The model also involves iterative queries, which suggests an element of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential security implications of the model, indicating a connection to computer security and cryptography (cs.CR).
